2026-06-16T04:22:00Z DEC public-widget-chat-notification-nonblocking
Decision: Public widget chat lead notifications must be non-blocking. A slow
or failed dealer notification may write a Teambox diagnostic later, but it
must not strand visitors on "Assistant is typing..." or keep the Send button
disabled.
Context: Final agent evals found Hyundai of Columbia and Ford of Columbia
public sales chat routes hanging on first message while Serra Honda, Serra
Nissan, Tony Serra Ford, and Serra Service passed. Root cause was the
best-effort notification path being awaited before the assistant reply.
Implementation:
- `src/routes/api/public/widget-chat.ts`: fire `notifyNewLead` and
  `notifyActiveConversation` in the background; append sent/not-delivered
  diagnostics to Teambox when the notification promise settles.
- `src/routes/w.$slug.tsx`: add a 30s browser-side AbortController cleanup so
  the public widget cannot leave the composer disabled after an upstream hang.
- `src/lib/console-renderers.tsx`: corrected InfoStore copy to say Semantic
  Guardian is available from Agents for internal canon/lineage/data-confidence
  questions.
- `src/test/inbound-lead-notify.test.ts`: added regression coverage proving
  widget chat responds even while lead notification is still pending.
